M&A in Emerging Countries Failing at Record Rate, Boersen Says

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-08-25T05:54:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/m-a-in-emerging-countries-failing-at-record-rate-boersen-says.html
Proposed mergers and acquisitions in
emerging economies have failed at record pace so far this year,
 Boersen-Zeitung  said, citing data provided by  Dealogic Holdings
Plc. (DL/)   Since the beginning of the year, 237 transactions announced
for a total value of $52.6 billion in  Brazil ,  India ,  Russia  and
 China  were called off, more than the previous record form 2008,
the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Richard Weiss  in  Frankfurt  at 
 rweiss5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at   bkammel@bloomberg.net . 